relevant_findings.general_examination: The patient was short but muscular (height 160.5 cm, weight 58.7 kg).
relevant_findings.genital_examination: The phallus was 8 cm long with severe chordee. The scrotum was bifid with a hypospadiac meatus in the perineum. A firm, tender mass measuring 3 x 8 cm was palpable in the neck of the left hemiscrotum, extending into the left inguinal canal. A small gonad was situated in the neck of the right hemiscrotum.
